## Methodology

### Pipeline Steps

1. **Brand Resolution** — Resolved "{{ brand_name }}" to OSM tags via brand lookup table
2. **Study Area** — {% if trade_area_mode == "buffer" %}Bounding box with buffer-based trade areas{% else %}Bounding box with isochrone-based trade areas{% endif %}
3. **POI Retrieval** — Queried OpenStreetMap via Overpass API for brand and competitor locations
4. **Trade Areas** — Computed {{ trade_area_mode }} trade areas around each brand location
5. **Demographic Enrichment** — Area-weighted Census ACS 5-year estimates at tract level
6. **Drive-Time Population** — Ring-differenced demographics at each travel-time threshold
7. **White Space Analysis** — Dissolved trade areas, subtracted from study area, ranked uncovered zones
8. **Candidate Generation** — Population-weighted centroids with minimum separation constraint
9. **Scoring** — Demand proxy: normalized population density x income index

### Data Sources

| Source | Vintage | Usage |
|--------|---------|-------|
| OpenStreetMap (Overpass API) | Current | Brand & competitor locations |
| US Census ACS 5-Year | 2022 | Demographics (population, income, age) |
| Census TIGER/Line | 2022 | Tract geometries |

